<p>GDP growth: 3.7% GDP: $1,926bn (PPP: $2,505bn) Inflation: 6.7% Population: 141.2m GDP per head: $13,650 (PPP: $17,750)</p>

<p>The country's political tag team, Vladimir Putin and Dmitry Medvedev, announced in September their intention to switch jobs yet again, another farcical step that has kept the presidency and prime ministership shuffling between the two. The actual election in March will be a formality, and a further sign of Russia's slide into authoritarianism. Public support for the two has waned as austerity has hurt living standards and highlighted perennially deep corruption. Economically, Russia's oil-fuelled resurgence will continue, though crude prices will fall.</p>

